On the other hand, High-Bandwidth Memory (HBM) has also emerged as a significant segment in the memory market, known for its increased bandwidth and energy efficiency. The stacked memory architecture of HBM allows for shorter communication paths and faster data transfer rates, making it ideal for applications that require handling large amounts of data such as artificial intelligence, gaming, and graphics processing units (GPUs). The demand for HBM is expected to continue to rise as the need for high-performance memory solutions grows across various industries.

